@adalca  Okay, thank you, I'll make use of the tutorial.

My understanding is that affine registration is limited to translation and/or rotation?  As my data is comprised of images that are displaced as I described earlier, I don't believe I require a model capable of deformable registration.  So yes, I wish to use affine registration.  

For my question regarding the code snippet: what I was trying to understand is what was the purpose of not using the simple affine_grid() function?  Does this not produce the required flow field?  Or is it because voxelmorph is capable of deformable registration and therefore affine_grid() would not be adequate?  I hope this makes my question clearer
